  Defined in header <stdio.h>        int feof( FILE *stream );
     Checks if the end of the given file stream has been reached.;Parameters,  stream   -   the file stream to check 
Return value,nonzero value if the end of the stream has been reached, otherwise ​0​;Notes,This function only reports the stream state as reported by the most recent I/O operation, it does not examine the associated data source. For example, if the most recent I/O was a fgetc, which returned the last byte of a file, feof returns zero. The next fgetc fails and changes the stream state to end-of-file. Only then feof returns non-zero.;In typical usage, input stream processing stops on any error; feof and ferror are then used to distinguish between different error conditions.;Example,

